 Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording in the gallery above, or read further here.JOHANNESBURG - Higher Education Minister Blade Nzimande briefed the media on the readiness of tertiary institutions for the new academic year.The Higher Education Department says it will pay particular attention to TVET colleges this year.Nzimande said he has received a list of grievances from the colleges which he wants to address.The minister held talks with various groups between 14 and 24 January.WATCH: No fee increases for NSFAS students, says NzimandeThere are 500,000 places available at tertiary institutions nationwide.Nzimande has previously indicated that the department was ready for the new academic year and is prepared for protests, should they erupt again.eNCA